5:
Milord, I've returned with the groceries
you requested.
9:
Great! Would you mind putting them 
away in the pantry for me? I've gotta 
keep an eye on the stove.
12:
Already done, Milord. I also went 
ahead and tidied up a bit—the dishes 
are all clean for whenever you're 
ready to start plating.
18:
Wow, you're already three-steps 
ahead! Thanks, Marianne.
31:
I'm amazed you can understand 
Nimbus' plans. All he ever says is stuff 
like "go!" or "Alk, left!"
36:
Sure, lemme ask the monsters to hold
still while I explain everything. 
I appreciate someone who can fight 
for themselves when I give the go.
41:
You don't have to walk me home... 
The Maids' Parlor is just up ahead.
45:
You're meeting with your maid friend 
for a performance review, right? We 
want to tell her how helpful you've 
been!
50:
Heh, looks like Alk and I are third 
wheels, huh?
53:
N-no, I can just walk myself home, 
that's all…
64:
Hmm? Can you smell the pub food 
already? If you're hungry, we can grab 
dinner after dropping off Marianne.
68:
Not now, dumbass, I smell something 
burning!
76:
This is weird... Where was everyone? 
You'd think people'd notice a fire that 
big, but there was no one around, not 
even the guard.
79:
Maybe one of the maids accidentally 
left an oven on?
83:
That was no accident. We've got a 
case of arson on our hands.
87:
I've seen it before. There's a band of 
mercenaries who kidnap hostages, 
then torch the place—and any 
incriminating evidence.
94:
Probably were. Can't imagine they 
came to thank me for all the times 
I foiled their plans.
97:
You may have noticed, but I've got 
military training. I served for years, 
and I honestly couldn't tell you how 
many enemies I've made myself.
104:
I left that life behind me after I... 
I messed up, BAD. It was supposed to 
be a solo infiltration mission, but I got 
caught.
108:
I barely escaped—was barely alive—
and then... she found me.
112:
She gave me a new life as a maid, 
a home, and... she gave me a new 
name—Marianne.
117:
I wanted to be her Marianne. I tried. 
I thought I could turn over a new leaf, 
and put all the battles behind me.
121:
But... I don't mind getting my hands 
bloody again if that's what it takes to 
bring her home.
125:
After this, I'd like to cancel my
 housekeeping contract. I can't work 
there if it puts her at risk.
129:
First things first. We've gotta go get 
her back.
133:
We're goin' with you. Do you know 
where to look?
141:
No excuses! We're not lettin' those 
thugs get away with trashing one of 
our favorite restaurants. ...We'll get 
her back. Right, Alk?
145:
Yeah, I'm sure there's a lot on your 
mind after the fire, but for now…
149:
We have to make sure your friend is 
safe! You can think about what to do 
from there later, okay?
157:
I've already pinned down their hideout
—it's not far. This ends TONIGHT!
161:
Just you wait...
Even if I have to leave "Marianne" 
behind—
